<section class="section wrap">
  <div class="eyebrow">Frameworks</div>
  <h1>Methodology, not just a resume.</h1>
  <p class="lead" style="max-width: 680px;">
    A resume lists what happened. This is how it happened. Three ways of working that
    show up across defense contracting, healthcare, EdTech, and enterprise SaaS, not
    proprietary to any single engagement, and reusable on the next one.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section section--border-top wrap">
  <div class="section-label">Framework 01</div>
  <h2>Governance as Infrastructure</h2>
  <p class="lead" style="max-width: 700px;">
    Compliance and ethics review belong inside the delivery pipeline from day one, not
    bolted on after legal finds the problem. Treating governance as infrastructure
    instead of a checkpoint is what lets AI systems ship on schedule and still hold up
    under scrutiny.
  </p>

  <figure class="diagram">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 900 260" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Comparison diagram of two delivery pipelines. The bolted-on pipeline runs design, build, and ship, then hits a legal review block that sends work back to build for rework. The built-in pipeline runs design, then build with governance embedded inside it, straight through to ship with no rework loop.">
      <g font-family="IBM Plex Sans, sans-serif">
        <text x="20" y="30" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#676E7C">BOLTED ON</text>
        <rect x="20" y="45" width="130" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="85" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Design</text>
        <rect x="190" y="45" width="130" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="255" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Build</text>
        <rect x="360" y="45" width="130" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="425" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Ship</text>
        <rect x="530" y="45" width="180" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FAEDEE" stroke="#BF1E2E" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="620" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#BF1E2E">Legal review</text>
        <text x="620" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#BF1E2E">blocks it</text>
        <path d="M150 73 L188 73" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw1a)"/>
        <path d="M320 73 L358 73" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw1a)"/>
        <path d="M490 73 L528 73" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw1a)"/>
        <path d="M620 101 C 620 130, 255 130, 255 103" fill="none" stroke="#BF1E2E" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4 3" marker-end="url(#fw1b)"/>
        <text x="437" y="145" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="10" letter-spacing="1" fill="#BF1E2E">REWORK LOOP</text>

        <text x="20" y="188" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#676E7C">BUILT IN</text>
        <rect x="20" y="203" width="130" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="85" y="236" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Design</text>
        <rect x="190" y="203" width="260" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FCF4F0" stroke="#D97443" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <text x="320" y="228" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Build, governance</text>
        <text x="320" y="245" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">embedded throughout</text>
        <rect x="580" y="203" width="130" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="645" y="236" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Ship</text>
        <path d="M150 231 L188 231" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw1a)"/>
        <path d="M450 231 L578 231" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw1a)"/>
        <defs>
          <marker id="fw1a" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="4" refY="4" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 Z" fill="#C2592A"/></marker>
          <marker id="fw1b" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="4" refY="4" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 Z" fill="#BF1E2E"/></marker>
        </defs>
      </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption class="small" style="text-align: center; color: var(--rg-ash); margin-top: 0.75rem;">Governance added after the fact creates a rework loop. Governance embedded in the build has no loop to fall into.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="callout co-insight">
    <div class="lbl">Key Insight</div>
    <p>Compliance and ethics review built into the pipeline from day one ships faster than bolting it on after legal finds the problem. The speed advantage isn't from skipping review, it's from never having to redo the work review would have caught.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="small" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--rg-ash);">Applied in:
