  </p>
</section>

<section class="section section--border-top wrap">
  <div class="section-label">Framework 02</div>
  <h2>Multi-Criteria Evaluation</h2>
  <p class="lead" style="max-width: 700px;">
    Whoever presents last in the room shouldn't win the decision. When a choice can be
    modeled, cost, integration risk, compliance fit, and scalability get scored against
    each other explicitly, before anyone pitches a preference.
  </p>

  <figure class="diagram">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 900 220" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Diagram showing four evaluation criteria, cost, integration risk, compliance fit, and scalability, each scored independently and feeding into a single weighted score, which produces a recommendation.">
      <g font-family="IBM Plex Sans, sans-serif">
        <rect x="20" y="20" width="180" height="64" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="110" y="57" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Cost</text>
        <rect x="240" y="20" width="180" height="64" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="330" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Integration</text>
        <text x="330" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Risk</text>
        <rect x="460" y="20" width="180" height="64" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="550" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Compliance</text>
        <text x="550" y="68" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Fit</text>
        <rect x="680" y="20" width="180" height="64" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="770" y="57" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Scalability</text>

        <path d="M110 84 L110 110 L450 110 L450 128" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
        <path d="M330 84 L330 110 L450 110" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
        <path d="M550 84 L550 110 L450 110" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
        <path d="M770 84 L770 110 L450 110" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#fw2)"/>
        <defs><marker id="fw2" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="4" refY="4" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 Z" fill="#C2592A"/></marker></defs>

        <rect x="345" y="130" width="210" height="50" rx="6" fill="#0A1128"/>
        <text x="450" y="161" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#FFCC00">WEIGHTED SCORE</text>
        <path d="M450 180 L450 200" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw2b)"/>
        <defs><marker id="fw2b" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="4" refY="4" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 Z" fill="#C2592A"/></marker></defs>
        <text x="450" y="216" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#676E7C">RECOMMENDATION</text>
      </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption class="small" style="text-align: center; color: var(--rg-ash); margin-top: 0.75rem;">Each criterion is scored on its own before any of them get combined into a recommendation.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="callout co-bottom">
    <div class="lbl">Bottom Line</div>
    <p>If a decision can be modeled, it should be. Multi-criteria frameworks beat whoever presents last in the room, because the criteria and their weights get agreed on before anyone has a favorite to defend.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="small" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--rg-ash);">Applied in:
    <a href="/work/ai-platform-architecture/" class="tag tag-ember" style="margin-right: 0.4rem;">20+ vendor EdTech evaluation</a>
    <a href="/work/emergency-services-modernization/" class="tag tag-ember">Emergency services vendor criteria</a>
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section section--border-top wrap">
  <div class="section-label">Framework 03</div>
  <h2>Bridge, Don't Translate</h2>
  <p class="lead" style="max-width: 700px;">
    A translator sits between two rooms, relaying and inevitably losing something in
    each handoff. A bridge sits in both rooms at once, fluent enough in engineering and
    the business that there's nothing left to lose in translation.
  </p>

  <figure class="diagram">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 900 260" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Two organizational models compared. The translator model shows engineering, a translator, and business connected in a sequential chain with information loss at each handoff. The bridge model shows engineering and business both connected directly to a single person fluent in both, with no sequential handoff.">
      <g font-family="IBM Plex Sans, sans-serif">
        <text x="20" y="28" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#676E7C">TRANSLATOR MODEL</text>
        <rect x="20" y="45" width="150" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="95" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Engineering</text>
        <rect x="220" y="45" width="150" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FAEDEE" stroke="#BF1E2E" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="295" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#BF1E2E">Translator</text>
        <rect x="420" y="45" width="150" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="495" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Business</text>
        <path d="M170 73 L218 73" stroke="#BF1E2E" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw3a)"/>
        <path d="M370 73 L418 73" stroke="#BF1E2E" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw3a)"/>
        <text x="194" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#BF1E2E">loss</text>
        <text x="394" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#BF1E2E">loss</text>
        <defs><marker id="fw3a" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="4" refY="4" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 Z" fill="#BF1E2E"/></marker></defs>

        <text x="20" y="168" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#676E7C">BRIDGE MODEL</text>
        <rect x="20" y="195" width="150" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="95" y="228" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Engineering</text>
        <rect x="420" y="195" width="150" height="56" rx="6" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#0A1128" stroke-opacity="0.15"/>
        <text x="495" y="228" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Business</text>
        <rect x="220" y="185" width="150" height="76" rx="6" fill="#FCF4F0" stroke="#D97443" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <text x="295" y="218" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">Fluent in</text>
        <text x="295" y="235" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#0A1128">both rooms</text>
        <path d="M170 223 L218 223" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw3b)"/>
        <path d="M370 223 L418 223" stroke="#C2592A" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#fw3b)"/>
        <defs><marker id="fw3b" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="4" refY="4" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L8,4 L0,8 Z" fill="#C2592A"/></marker></defs>
      </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption class="small" style="text-align: center; color: var(--rg-ash); margin-top: 0.75rem;">A translator relays between two rooms. A bridge is fluent enough to sit in both at once.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="callout co-note">
    <div class="lbl">Note</div>
    <p>I don't translate between engineering and the business, I sit in both rooms well enough that translation isn't necessary. That only works with real fluency on both sides, a PhD in Systems Engineering on one end and 16+ years of product and stakeholder work on the other.</p>
  </div>

